    >>>>> "Alexandre" == Alexandre Hautequest <hquest@linuxbr.com.br> writes:
        >> Suggestions?  Is this something I did wrong or is it a bug
        >> somewhere?
        Alexandre> try an "echo [Ctrl]v [Esc]c"... some things are solved
        Alexandre> with this...
    It didn't for me... I had to log in on ssh, and reboot the machine...
Yes, Esc c is a console reset that roughly speaking should not
touch the keyboard side. For some obscure reason a few kbd things
are reset by it nevertheless.
But reboot -- what a bad habit, when you have source..
Next time, try, e.g., "kbd_mode -a".
